---
import MainHead from '../components/MainHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer/index.jsx';
import Nav from '../components/Nav/index.jsx';
import FamPic from "../../public/assets/pictures/familyPose.png";

---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <MainHead title="About | Jose Ulices Perez Jr." />
    <style lang="scss">
      .heroImg {
        object-fit: cover;

        img {
          width: 100%;
          height: 100%;
        }
      }

      .bio {
        font-size: var(--f-u1);
        line-height: 2;
      }

      .title {
        font-size: 28px;
        font-style: oblique;
        font-weight: 700;
      }

      .williamLink {
        color: #05091e;
        text-decoration: none;
        transition: ease-out;
        transition-duration: .125s;
      }
      .williamLink:hover {
        color: var(--c-blue);
        transition: ease-in;
        transition-duration: .125s;
        font-style: oblique;
        font-weight: 500;
        font-size: 22px;
        text-decoration: underline;
        
      }
      .signContainer{
        width: 100%;
      }

      .signContent {
        width: 100%;
        height: 350px;
      }
      #signature {
        stroke-dasharray: 1130;
        stroke-dashoffset: 1130;
        animation: sign 4.5s ease;
        animation-fill-mode: forwards;
        animation-iteration-count: infinite;
        
      }
      @keyframes sign {
        
        80%, 100%  {
          stroke-dashoffset: 0;  
        }
      }

    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <Nav />
    <div class="wrapper">
      <h1>About Mr. Perez</h1>
      <div class="heroImg">
        <img width="1400" height="350" src={FamPic} />
      </div>
      <div class="bio wrapper wrapper__readable mt8">
        
          <p class="title">
            Hello World!

          </p>
        
        <p>
          I’m a full-stack web developer from Norwalk, California. I graduated from UCLA earning my certificate in Full-Stack Web Development in December 2020. Shoutout to my amazing instructor  <a title="UCLA Coding Instructor" class="williamLink" href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/williamavasquez/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">William Vasquez</a> for teaching me technical skills such as <span style="color: var(--c-red);">React</span> or <span style="color: var(--c-red);">Javascript</span> but also, for teaching me to be a problem solver and to never give up. 

        </p>
        <p>
A little about me, I am a diligent work professional that brings a positive attitude every day. I love to work while welcoming any challenge with open arms. I believe two brains are better than one and value teamwork. I’m a compassionate, helpful, determined individual who puts 110% into everything I do. My best work has been with a team and I’m proud to say that. 
          
        </p>
        <p>
        My hobbies inlcude playing video games when I can. Right now, I am playing Heroes Of The Storm, Call of Duty Warzone, and Clash Royale. I enjoy watching sports such as basketball, baseball, football, and hockey. I go for all the L.A. teams except the Angels. When I can, I also enjoy shooting and editing photos/videos. Currently, I use the Canon T7i to capture, Photoshop CS6 and Sony Vegas Pro 15 to edit. 
        </p>
        <p>
          When it comes to Web Development, I’m passionate in creating functional user interfaces that embrace the art of simplicity. Focusing on making each single component on the page serve a purpose. I also keep up with the latest web trends and incorporate them into my designs. 

        </p>

        <p>
        Sincerely,
        </p>

